title: Appreciation Ceremony for Electronic Health Record Internship Programme held (with photos)
content_text:
p>
					Eleven organisations and 19 interns participating in the 
					Electronic Health Record (eHR) Internship Programme were 
					presented with certificates of appreciation at a ceremony 
					today (November 4) as commendation of their efforts and 
					support for the Government in promoting an eHR sharing 
					system in Hong Kong. The eHR Internship Programme is a three-year project 
					launched by the Government in 2014 as part of the 
					development roadmap of the territory-wide eHR Sharing System

development roadmap of the territory-wide eHR Sharing System 
					(eHRSS) rolled out in March 2016. Under the programme, internship placements are provided by 
					participating organisations to graduates of 
					healthcare-related and IT disciplines. The objective is to 
					provide interns with training and practical experience in 
					eHR and to encourage private and non-governmental 
					organisations to take part in eHR-related activities. Hong 
					Kong Cyberport Management Company Limited has been engaged

Kong Cyberport Management Company Limited has been engaged 
					as the Secretariat to provide administration and 
					implementation services for the programme. A spokesman for the Food and Health Bureau said, "The 
					programme has planted a seed in building up the health 
					informatics capacity in Hong Kong and encouraging private 
					sector participation in eHR sharing, which is crucial to the 
					success of eHRSS implementation. "As at today, more than 1,000 private healthcare provider

organisations have registered with eHRSS and over 300,000 
					members of the public have joined the system. The Government 
					looks forward to continuous support from the private sector 
					and the community for eHRSS." Following the certificate presentation, a kick-off ceremony 
					was held to mark the commencement of a community roving 
					exhibition to promote eHRSS and showcase the achievements of 
					the eHR Internship Programme. The exhibition will be carried out until December 10 at

seven venues, namely Cyberport, Tin Chak Shopping Centre, 
					Tai Po Mega Mall, Kwun Tong MTR Station, Olympian City, 
					InnoCentre and Youth Square. Registration booths will also 
					be set up at selected venues for the public to register with 
					eHRSS on site.
